summary: "This is a ready-to-use catalogue of 18 asynchronous English
  language assessments spanning three age groups (kids 5–11, teens 12–17,
  adults 18+) and CEFR levels A1 through B2. Each assessment covers speaking,
  reading, or writing and is fully self-contained: student-facing tasks,
  visual supports, teacher notes with setup and differentiation guidance, and
  a detailed scoring rubric. The catalogue also includes general master
  rubrics for speaking and writing that can be applied across assessments,
  plus a full quick-reference table listing all 18 tests by age, level,
  skill, type, time, and points."
problem: "Teachers who need to assess speaking, reading, and writing across
  different ages and proficiency levels often have to build assessments from
  scratch, cobble together inconsistent rubrics, or rely on generic tests
  that don't reflect authentic, real-world language use. Async speaking
  assessment in particular is hard to design well without clear scoring
  criteria. This catalogue solves that by providing a complete, tested bank
  of age- and level-appropriate assessments with built-in rubrics, teacher
  notes, and differentiation tips — removing prep time while keeping
  assessment quality high and consistent."
